              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22275854-summer?shelf=paranormal-angels-demons">paranormal-angels-demons</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1083718413" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10159181290344577542"><b>This is a NOVELLA, not a novel.</b> Maybe I missed that in the description, but I thought it was a complete book. And where it cuts off is right when it starts to be enjoyable. :(<br/>That aside, I still had problems with this <i>book</i>. It felt like Bellingeri had this great dream, woke up, and had to get it on paper. But once she got it on paper, she didn&apos;t bother to make it great. Sure she checked for spelling and grammatical errors, but we&apos;re TOLD everything. You won&apos;t FEEL or EXPERIENCE a single scene. R</span>
  <span id="freeText10159181290344577542" style="display:none"><b>This is a NOVELLA, not a novel.</b> Maybe I missed that in the description, but I thought it was a complete book. And where it cuts off is right when it starts to be enjoyable. :(<br />That aside, I still had problems with this <i>book</i>. It felt like Bellingeri had this great dream, woke up, and had to get it on paper. But once she got it on paper, she didn't bother to make it great. Sure she checked for spelling and grammatical errors, but we're TOLD everything. You won't FEEL or EXPERIENCE a single scene. Really disappointing because the story she has in her head sounds AMAZING!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10159181290344577542" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
